    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-01T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-01T21:00:00-05:00" n="575"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.857/160a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-01T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 1, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2460. The Navy Department advises that inquiries have been received from
                    representatives of the Brazilian Navy concerning charges to be claimed by the
                    United States Navy for assisting in the salvage of the Brazilian Naval Cruiser
                        <hi rend="italic">Rio Grande do Sul</hi> near Recife.</p>
                <p>You are directed to inform the appropriate Brazilian authorities that any rights
                    accruing to the United States Government by reason of the salvaging of the <hi
                        rend="italic">Rio Grande do Sul</hi> are waived.</p>
                <p>For your own information and not for incorporation in your official communication
                    to the Brazilian Government, this decision was made because <list>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                        <item>no commercial interests are involved, and</item>
                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                        <item>this same exceptional treatment was accorded the Argentine vessel <hi
                                rend="italic">Victoria</hi> in April, 1942.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Please communicate with the Department as soon as the reaction of the Brazilian
                    Government is known, since the Navy Department requests confirmation of the
                    waiver.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
